Apple recently updated the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipad-pro/">iPad Pro</a>, widening the gap with the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipad-air/">iPad Air</a>, but how different are the two product lines and which should you buy?<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/03/iPad-Pro-2024-vs-Air-2024-Feature.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-998397" /><br/>
Earlier this year, Apple refreshed the &zwnj;iPad Air&zwnj; with the M3 chip—a minor update over the previous model from 2024 which added the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/m2/">M2</a> chip and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/apple-pencil/">Apple Pencil</a> hover. The latest &zwnj;iPad Pro&zwnj; models introduced the M5 chip alongside a small number of changes after last year's major redesign, which saw the debut of a thinner design with OLED displays.<br/>
<br/>
Should you consider purchasing the &zwnj;iPad Air&zwnj; to save money, or do you need the high-end features of the &zwnj;iPad Pro&zwnj;? Our guide answers the question of how to decide which of these two iPads is best for you.<br/>
